     ).toLowerCase();\\n      const author = cp.commitAuthorUsername?.toLowerCase() ?? \\\"\\\";\\n      return displayedTitle.includes(query) || author.includes(query);\\n    })\\n  : allCheckpoints;\\n```\\n\\n**Search Input Component:**\\n- Uses Input component with SearchIcon (lines 209-216)\\n- `placeholder=\\\"Search checkpoints...\\\"`\\n- Filters on user prompt OR commit message OR commit author\\n- Case-insensitive substring matching\\n\\n**Key Files for Search:**\\n1. `/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.tsx` - Main checkpoint list page with search input\\n2. `/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/components/CheckpointSidebar.tsx` - Session/file tree sidebar\\n3. `/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/components/FilesSection.tsx` - File diff viewer with expandable files\\n4. `/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/api.ts` - API types and fetch functions\\n5. `/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/hooks/useCommitsQuery.ts` - React Query hooks\\n\\n### 3. API Routes Structure\\n\\n**API Base:** `GET /api/v1/cache/{org}/{repo}/checkpoints?branch={branch}&limit={limit}`\\n\\n**Backend Implementation:** `/entire.io/api/src/routes/cache.ts` (lines 1236-1374)\\n\\n**Key Parameters:**\\n- `branch` - Filter by branch (default: \\\"main\\\")\\n- `limit` - Pagination limit (default: 100)\\n- `source` - Optional \\\"github\\\" to trigger sync (local dev only)\\n\\n**Response Type (CheckpointsResponse):**\\n```typescript\\n{\\n  checkpoints: CheckpointInfo[];\\n  repo_full_name: string;\\n  updated_at: string;\\n  from_cache: boolean;\\n  app_has_access: boolean | null;\\n  session_branch_exists: boolean | null;\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Data Types & Interfaces\\n\\n**CheckpointInfo** (from `/api/src/routes/cache.ts`, lines 71-114):\\n- `commitSha`, `commitMessage`, `commitAuthor`, `commitAuthorUsername`, `commitDate`\\n- `additions`, `deletions`, `filesChanged`, `filesTouched`\\n- `fileStats` - Array of FileStats with per-file diffs\\n- `checkpointId` - Maps to metadata on checkpoint branch\\n- `sessions` - Array of SessionInfo\\n- `sessionCount`, `totalSteps`, `agents` - Aggregated metrics\\n- `inputTokens`, `outputTokens`, `cacheCreationTokens`, `outputTokens`, `apiCallCount`\\n- `attribution` - Line-level attribution metrics\\n\\n**SessionInfo:**\\n```typescript\\n{\\n  prompt: string | null;      // User prompt for this session\\n  agent: string;              // Agent name (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\")\\n  steps: number;              // Step count\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Component Hierarchy\\n\\n**CheckpointsPage.tsx** (Main list page)\\n- Branch selector (Combobox dropdown)\\n- Search input (Input with SearchIcon)\\n- Checkpoint list (ListView with CheckpointsList component)\\n  - CheckpointsList → Maps checkpoints to ListViewItem rows\\n  - Each row displays: title, metadata (ID, date, author, agent), stats (additions/deletions/file count/sessions/tokens)\\n\\n**CheckpointDetailPage.tsx** (Detail view)\\n- SessionDetail component for transcript view\\n- CheckpointSidebar component (sessions/files tree)\\n- FilesSection component (diff viewer)\\n\\n**CheckpointSidebar.tsx:**\\n- Sessions section - Card list of sessions with step count and preview\\n- Files section - Tree view of modified files with status badges and line counts\\n\\n**FilesSection.tsx:**\\n- Expandable file cards showing diffs\\n- FileCard component with status badge and line counts\\n\\n### 6. Routing\\n\\n**Checkpoint Routes (File-based):**\\n- `/gh/$org/$repo/checkpoints/$branch/` - Checkpoint list page\\n- `/gh/$org/$repo/checkpoints/$branch/$checkpointId` - Checkpoint detail page\\n\\n**Route Loaders:**\\n- `repoIndexLoader()` - Redirects to default branch\\n- `checkpointsBranchLoader()` - Validates repo access\\n- `checkpointsIndexLoader()` - Fetches checkpoints and handles stale branch redirects\\n\\n### 7. Search/Filter Query Hooks\\n\\n**useCheckpointsQuery** (hooks/useCommitsQuery.ts, lines 42-48):\\n```typescript\\nexport function useCheckpointsQuery(org: string, repo: string, branch: string = \\\"main\\\") {\\n  return useQuery<CheckpointsResponse>({\\n    queryKey: [\\\"github\\\", \\\"checkpoints\\\", org, repo, branch],\\n    queryFn: () => fetchCheckpoints(org, repo, branch),\\n    staleTime: 5 * 60 * 1000, // 5 minutes\\n  });\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Additional Hooks:**\\n- `useCheckpointStatusQuery()` - Fast status check (checkpoint_count, app_has_access)\\n- `useBranchesQuery()` - Branch list for selector dropdown\\n- `useCheckpointTranscriptQuery()` - Fetch full transcript for detail view\\n- `useResolveCheckpointQuery()` - Resolve checkpoint location after branch deletion\\n\\n### 8. Empty States & Error Handling\\n\\n**Empty State Conditions:**\\n1. App doesn't have GitHub access - Show \\\"Grant access\\\" button\\n2. App has access but no session branch - Show CLI installation steps\\n3. App has access and session branch exists but no checkpoints on branch - Show \\\"No checkpoints on this branch\\\"\\n4. No search results - Show \\\"No matching checkpoints\\\"\\n\\n**Error Handling:**\\n- Auth errors trigger ReauthenticateState component\\n- 404 errors (repo/branch not found) show NotFoundContent\\n- Generic errors show error message in bordered container\\n\\n### 9. API Client Architecture\\n\\n**Request Function** (`/src/lib/api/client.ts`):\\n- Base URL resolution (dev: `localhost:8787`, prod: `https://entire.io`)\\n- CSRF token handling (double-submit cookie pattern)\\n- JSON response parsing\\n- Error normalization with custom ApiError class\\n- Credentials included by default\\n\\n### 10. Key Features Currently Implemented\\n\\n- Client-side search filtering (prompt, commit message, author)\\n- Branch selector dropdown\\n- Pagination via limit parameter\\n- Checkpoint status quick-check endpoint\\n- Token usage metrics display\\n- Attribution metrics (line-level contribution tracking)\\n- File diff view with expandable sections\\n- Session transcript viewer\\n- Agent badges with color coding\\n- Rel