ng,\\n  endDate: string,\\n  limit: number = 500,\\n): Promise<UserCheckpoint[]>\\n\\nexport async function findCheckpointById(\\n  db: Kysely<DB>,\\n  repoId: string,\\n  checkpointId: string,\\n  defaultBranch: string = \\\"main\\\",\\n): Promise<CheckpointLocation | null>\\n```\\n\\n**Current Query Strategy:**\\n- Uses **Kysely** (TypeScript SQL query builder) for MySQL/PlanetScale\\n- Implements **\\\"Deferred Join\\\"** pattern to avoid PlanetScale sort buffer OOM when ordering by large JSON columns (`file_stats`)\\n- Queries are indexed by `(repo_id, branch, commit_date)` and `(commit_author_github_id, commit_date)`\\n- **No full-text search or filtering beyond basic WHERE clauses**\\n\\n**Example from getCheckpointsForBranch:**\\n```typescript\\n// Step 1: Sort/limit by ID only (avoids sort buffer OOM)\\nconst idRows = await db\\n  .selectFrom(\\\"repo_checkpoint_commits\\\")\\n  .select(\\\"id\\\")\\n  .where(\\\"repo_id\\\", \\\"=\\\", repoId)\\n  .where(\\\"branch\\\", \\\"=\\\", branch)\\n  .orderBy(\\\"commit_date\\\", \\\"desc\\\")\\n  .limit(limit)\\n  .execute();\\n\\n// Step 2: Fetch full data without ORDER BY (preserves sort from step 1)\\nconst rows = await db\\n  .selectFrom(\\\"repo_checkpoint_commits as cc\\\")\\n  .leftJoin(\\\"repo_checkpoints as cp\\\", ...)\\n  .where(\\\"cc.id\\\", \\\"in\\\", idRows.map((r) => r.id))\\n  .execute();\\n```\\n\\n### 4. **Checkpoint Data Types**\\n\\nFrom `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/src/lib/db/checkpoints.ts`:\\n\\n```typescript\\nexport interface CheckpointWithCommit {\\n  checkpoint_id: string;\\n  branch: string | null;\\n  prompt: string | null;              // User's prompt - searchable\\n  agent: string;                       // Agent name\\n  steps: number;\\n  session_count: number;\\n  strategy: string | null;\\n  created_at: string | null;\\n  commit_sha: string | null;\\n  commit_message: string | null;       // Commit message - searchable\\n  commit_author: string | null;\