`api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts`)\\n\\nThin wrapper around Turbopuffer's REST API using `fetch()`. No SDK needed.\\n\\n```typescript\\n// Query Turbopuffer for checkpoint search\\n// Uses FTS (full-text search) on the `text` attribute\\n// Returns checkpoint_ids ranked by relevance\\nexport async function searchCheckpoints(\\n  apiKey: string,\\n  repoId: string,\\n  query: string,\\n  filters?: { branch?: string; agent?: string; author?: string },\\n  limit?: number,\\n): Promise<SearchResult[]>\\n```\\n\\n**Turbopuffer REST endpoint**: `POST https://api.turbopuffer.com/v1/vectors/checkpoints-{repo_id}/query`\\n\\n**Request body** — use BM25 full-text search on `text` field + optional attribute filters:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"top_k\\\": 50,\\n  \\\"rank_by\\\": [\\\"text\\\", \\\"BM25\\\", \\\"search query here\\\"],\\n  \\\"filters\\\": {\\n    \\\"branch\\\": [[\\\"Eq\\\", \\\"main\\\"]]\\n  },\\n  \\\"include_attributes\\\": [\\\"checkpoint_id\\\", \\\"branch\\\", \\\"agent\\\", \\\"author\\\", \\\"created_at\\\", \\\"commit_sha\\\", \\\"commit_message\\\", \\\"prompt\\\", \\\"files_touched\\\"]\\n}\\n```\\n\\nReturns `checkpoint_id` values which we use to fetch full checkpoint data from PlanetScale.\\n\\n### 2. Env Update (`api/src/env.ts`)\\n\\nAdd `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY?: string` as optional to the `Env` interface. Not added to `REQUIRED_ENV_VARS` since search is an optional feature — the endpoint returns 503 if the key is missing.\\n\\n### 3. Search API Endpoint (`api/src/routes/cache.ts`)\\n\\nNew route: `GET /:org/:repo/checkpoints/search?q=<query>&branch=<branch>`\\n\\n**Flow**:\\n1. Validate `q` param (required, non-empty)\\n2. Check repo access (reuse `checkRepoAccess()`)\\n3. Call `searchCheckpoints()` with `repoRecord.id` and query\\n4. Get the `checkpoint_id` list from results\\n5. Fetch full checkpoint data from PlanetScale using `db.checkpoints.getByIds(repoId, checkpointIds)`\\n6. Map through `mapCheckpointToInfo()` (reuse existing mapper)\\n7. Return in