n\\n## New Dependencies\\n\\nAdd to `entire.io/api/package.json`:\\n```\\n\\\"@turbopuffer/turbopuffer\\\": \\\"^0.2.x\\\"\\n\\\"openai\\\": \\\"^4.x\\\"\\n```\\n\\nThese are used by the script only (not the Worker). They're devDependencies since the Worker doesn't need them at runtime yet (real-time indexing will add them to dependencies later).\\n\\n## Document Schema in Turbopuffer\\n\\nOne namespace per repo: `checkpoints-{repo_id}`\\n\\nEach document:\\n```\\nid:               uint   (auto-incrementing, derived from row order)\\ncheckpoint_id:    string (12-hex-char, for linking back to frontend route)\\nbranch:           string (for filtering)\\nagent:            string (for filtering)\\nauthor:           string (commit_author_username, for filtering)\\ncreated_at:       string (ISO timestamp, for sorting/filtering)\\ncommit_sha:       string (for display)\\ncommit_message:   string (stored for FTS)\\nprompt:           string (stored for FTS)\\nfiles_touched:    string (comma-joined paths, for FTS)\\ntext:             string (concatenated searchable text, for FTS + vector)\\n```\\n\\nThe `text` field is what gets embedded. It's a concatenation of:\\n```\\nPrompt: {prompt}\\nCommit: {commit_message}\\nFiles: {files_touched joined by \\\", \\\"}\\nTranscript: {first user message + first assistant response, if available}\\n```\\n\\n## Embedding Model\\n\\nOpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` (1536 dimensions). Cheap, fast, good enough for POC. ~$0.02 per 1M tokens.\\n\\n## Script Flow\\n\\n```\\n1. Connect to PlanetScale\\n2. Query all repos with checkpoint_count > 0\\n3. For each repo:\\n   a. Create/get Turbopuffer namespace `checkpoints-{repo_id}`\\n   b. Query all checkpoints + commits for this repo (joined)\\n   c. Optionally fetch transcript excerpts from GitHub (--with-transcripts)\\n   d. Construct text field for each checkpoint\\n   e. Generate embeddings in batches (OpenAI batch API, 50 at a time)\\n   f. Upsert to Turbopuffer in batches\\n   g. Log progress\\n4. Print summary stats\\n```\\n\\n### CLI Arguments\\n\\n```\\nnpx tsx scripts/backfill-search.ts [options]\\n\\nOptions:\\n  --repo <full_name>     Only backfill a specific repo (e.g., \\\"entireio/cli\\\")\\n  --with-transcripts     Fetch transcript excerpts from GitHub (slower, needs GITHUB_TOKEN)\\n  --dry-run              Show what would be indexed without writing to Turbopuffer\\n  --limit <n>            Max checkpoints per repo (for testing)\\n```\\n\\n### Transcript Fetching (--with-transcripts)\\n\\nWhen enabled, for each checkpoint:\\n1. Compute folder path: `{checkpoint_id[:2]}/{checkpoint_id[2:]}`\\n2. Fetch `{folder}/0/full.jsonl` from `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch via GitHub API\\n3. Parse with the appropriate agent transcript parser (reuse `getParserForAgent()`)\\n4. Extract first user message content + first assistant message content\\n5. Truncate to ~2000 chars combined to stay within embedding token limits\\n6. Append to the `text` field\\n\\nThis uses `GITHUB_TOKEN` (a PAT with repo read access). Rate limited to ~5000 req/hr. For repos with many checkpoints, this is the bottleneck — add a small delay between requests.\\n\\n## Files to Create/Modify\\n\\n| File | Action | Description |\\n|------|--------|-------------|\\n| `api/scripts/backfill-search.ts` | **Create** | Main backfill script (~200 lines) |\\n| `api/package.json` | **Modify** | Add `@turbopuffer/turbopuffer` and `openai` to devDependencies |\\n\\n### `backfill-search.ts` Structure\\n\\n```typescript\\n// 1. Imports & config\\n// 2. parseArgs() - CLI argument parsing\\n// 3. buildSearchText(checkpoint, transcriptExcerpt?) - construct text for embedding\\n// 4. generateEmbeddings(texts[]) - batch call to OpenAI\\n// 5. fetchTranscriptExcerpt(repoFullName, checkpointId, token) - GitHub API + parser\\n// 6. processRepo(db, repoId, repoFullName, options) - main per-repo logic\\n// 7. main() - orchestrator\\n```\\n\\nKey implementation details:\\n\\n- **DB query**: Join `repo_checkpoints` + `repo_checkpoint_commits` grouped by checkpoint_id (same pattern as `getCheckpointsForBranch` in `src/lib/planetscale/checkpoints.ts`)\\n- **Embedding batching**: OpenAI allows up to 2048 embeddings per request, but we batch at 50 to limit memory and provide progress feedback\\n- **Turbopuffer upsert**: Batch upsert with vectors + attributes. Turbopuffer's `upsert()` handles create-or-update automatically\\n- **Transcript parsers**: Import and reuse `getParserForAgent()` from `src/lib/transcript-parsers/`\\n- **GitHub API**: Reuse the same raw fetch pattern as `fetchFileAtCommit()` in `src/lib/github.ts`\\n- **Progress logging**: Log per-repo progress (checkpoints indexed, time taken)\\n- **Error handling**: Skip individual checkpoints on error (log warning), don't abort the whole repo\\n\\n## Example Usage\\n\\n```bash\\n# Backfill a single repo (quick test)\\nDATABASE_URL=mysql://... TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY=... OPENAI_API_KEY=... \\\\\\n  npx tsx scripts/backfill-search.ts --repo entireio/cli --limit 10\\n\\n# Backfill all repos, metadata only (no transcripts)\\nDATABASE_URL=mysql://... TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY=... OPENAI_API_KEY=... \\\\\\n  npx tsx scripts/backfill-search.ts\\n\\n# Backfill all repos with transcript excerpts\\nDATABASE_URL=mysql://... TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY=... OPENAI_API_KEY=... GITHUB_TOKEN=... \\\\\\n  npx tsx scripts/backfill-search.ts --with-transcripts\\n\\n# Dry run to see what would be indexed\\nDATABASE_URL=mysql://... TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY=... OPENAI_API_KEY=... \\\\\\n  npx tsx scripts/backfill-search.ts --dry-run\\n```\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Run with `--dry-run --repo <your-test-repo>` to verify data extraction looks correct\\n2. Run with `--repo <your-test-repo> --limit 5` to index a small batch\\n3. Verify in Turbopuffer dashboard that the namespace exists with correct document count\\n4. Test search manually via Turbopuffer API/dashboard to confirm FTS + vector results return relevant checkpoints\\n5. Run full backfill once satisfied\\n\",\"numLines\":155,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":155}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"27f07b7f-aa20-45da-98fe-016d0f7692bf\"}\n{\"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"7ed56db1-2e87-4014-8b32-2e53e620cc1b\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"ca8718d4-7ea1-4944-9707-1478929afa10\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/scripts/backfill-search.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"37930971e673b52e@v5\",\"version\":5,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T03:39:46.014Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/package.json\":{\"backupFileName\":\"af24d0118b6cc8b1@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-03T23:42:24.013Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/.claude/plans/resilient-squishing-fern.md\":{\"backupFileName\":\"cdbadcbe5f5d68a2@v1\",\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T05:24:37.361Z\"}},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T03:39:46.013Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":true}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"631c1549-4f16-4981-8cef-56590f2fd747\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"504a5988-0478-439b-bb41-a58eeaef723a\",\"version\":\"2.1.56\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"resilient-squishing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01VULVXfbYUgnxXF8bHoRfLM\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01RsaJD9W8t4arFYwVZFYf8h\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/.claude/plans/resilient-squishing-fern.md\",\"content\":\"# Wire Up Checkpoint Search via Turbopuffer\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCheckpoints have been backfilled into Turbopuffer (namespace `checkpoints-{repo_id}`) with embeddings and attributes. The frontend currently does client-side string matching over prompts, commit messages, and authors. We need to:\\n\\n1. Add a search API endpoint that queries Turbopuffer\\n2. Replace the frontend's client-side filtering with API-driven search\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\n- **API**: