uffer.ts`)\\n\\nThin wrapper around Turbopuffer's REST API using `fetch()`. No SDK needed.\\n\\n```typescript\\nexport interface TurbopufferSearchResult {\\n  checkpoint_id: string;\\n  // other attributes returned for convenience\\n}\\n\\nexport async function searchCheckpoints(\\n  apiKey: string,\\n  repoId: string,\\n  query: string,\\n  filters?: { branch?: string },\\n  limit?: number,\\n): Promise<TurbopufferSearchResult[]>\\n```\\n\\n**Turbopuffer REST endpoint**: `POST https://api.turbopuffer.com/v1/vectors/checkpoints-{repo_id}/query`\\n\\n**Request body** — use BM25 full-text search on the `text` attribute + optional attribute filters:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"top_k\\\": 50,\\n  \\\"rank_by\\\": [\\\"text\\\", \\\"BM25\\\", \\\"search query here\\\"],\\n  \\\"filters\\\": {\\n    \\\"branch\\\": [[\\\"Eq\\\", \\\"main\\\"]]\\n  },\\n  \\\"include_attributes\\\": [\\\"checkpoint_id\\\"]\\n}\\n```\\n\\nReturns `checkpoint_id` values which we use to fetch full checkpoint data from PlanetScale.\\n\\n### 2. Env Update (`api/src/env.ts`)\\n\\nAdd `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY?: string` as optional to the `Env` interface. Not added to `REQUIRED_ENV_VARS` since search is an optional feature — the endpoint returns 503 if the key is missing.\\n\\n### 3. Search API Endpoint (`api/src/routes/cache.ts`)\\n\\nNew route on `repoRoutes`: `GET /:org/:repo/checkpoints/search?q=<query>&branch=<branch>`\\n\\n**Flow**:\\n1. Validate `q` param (required, non-empty)\\n2. Check repo access (reuse existing `checkRepoAccess()` helper)\\n3. If `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` not set, return 503\\n4. Call `searchCheckpoints()` with `repoRecord.id`, query, and optional branch filter\\n5. Get the `checkpoint_id` list from results\\n6. Fetch full checkpoint data from PlanetScale using existing `db.checkpoints.getByIds(repoId, checkpointIds)`\\n7. Map through existing `mapCheckpointToInfo()` to build response\\n8. Return in same shape as the existing checkpoints endpoint for frontend compatibility\\n\\n**Auth**: Same `optionalAuth + rateLimitUnauthenticated` pattern as existing checkpoint routes.\\n\\n**Response**: Same `CheckpointsResponse` type so the frontend can render search results identically to the normal list.\\n\\n### 4. Frontend API Function (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/api.ts`)\\n\\nAdd:\\n```typescript\\nexport async function searchCheckpoints(\\n  org: string, repo: string, query: string, branch?: string,\\n): Promise<CheckpointsResponse> {\\n  const params = new URLSearchParams({ q: query });\\n  if (branch) params.set(\\\"branch\\\", branch);\\n  return request<CheckpointsResponse>(\\n    `/api/v1/cache/${org}/${repo}/checkpoints/search?${params.toString()}`\\n  );\\n}\\n```\\n\\nReuses the existing `CheckpointsResponse` type — no new response types needed.\\n\\n### 5. Frontend Hook (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/hooks/useCommitsQuery.ts`)\\n\\nAdd:\\n```typescript\\nexport function useSearchCheckpointsQuery(\\n  org: string, repo: string, query: string, branch: string,\\n) {\\n  return useQuery<CheckpointsResponse>({\\n    queryKey: [\\\"github\\\", \\\"checkpoints-search\\\", org, repo, query, branch],\\n    queryFn: () => searchCheckpoints(org, repo, query, branch),\\n    enabled: query.trim().length > 0,\\n    staleTime: 30_000,\\n    placeholderData: (prev) => prev, // keep previous results while fetching\\n  });\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 6. Frontend Page (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.tsx`)\\n\\nReplace the client-side filter block (lines 82-95) with debounced API search:\\n\\n- Add `useEffect`-based debounce (300ms) on `searchQuery` → `debouncedQuery`\\n- Call `useSearchCheckpointsQuery(org, repo, debouncedQuery, branch)`\\n- When `debouncedQuery` is non-empty, use search results; otherwise use normal checkpoint list\\n- Show subtle loading indicator while search is in flight\\n- Update \\\"No matching checkpoints\\\" empty state to work with search results\\n\\nKey changes:\\n- Remove: the 